Specifically, the hook lifecycle pattern used under `hooks/` in this
repository — request-risk classification, a pre-tool-use block-list for a
small set of destructive local actions, a post-tool-use tool-use evidence
ledger, and a capped stop-gate that requires verification evidence before a
turn can be reported as complete — is adapted from fable-ish Codex's hook
design (`hooks/user_prompt_submit.py`, `hooks/pre_tool_use.py`,
`hooks/post_tool_use.py`, `hooks/stop_gate.py` in the upstream repository).

